# Cursor Rules for Fantasy Football Analyzer Project

## LEGACY FILE PROTECTION
- NEVER modify fantasy_analyzer.py - this is a legacy file
- All new development must use the modular system (fantasy_analyzer_new.py and modules/)
- If you need to make changes, use the modular system components

## MODULAR SYSTEM USAGE
- Use fantasy_analyzer_new.py as the main entry point
- All test scripts should import from fantasy_analyzer_new, not fantasy_analyzer
- Data loading: modules/data_loader.py
- Scoring: modules/scoring_engine.py  
- ML models: modules/ml_models.py
- Player analysis: modules/player_analysis.py
- League analysis: modules/league_analysis.py
- Value analysis: modules/value_analysis.py
- Reporting: modules/reporting.py
- Utilities: modules/utils.py

## TESTING
- All test scripts should use the modular system
- Update any existing test scripts to import from fantasy_analyzer_new
- Use test_modular_system.py as the main testing script

## CONSTANTS AND CONFIGURATION
- Use config/constants.py for all constants and configurations
- Do not hardcode values in individual modules

## ERROR HANDLING
- If you encounter issues with the legacy system, fix them in the modular system
- Never modify fantasy_analyzer.py to fix issues
- Use the modular system's enhanced error handling and data loading

## GIT PROTECTION
- The legacy file is already in .gitignore to prevent accidental commits
- Always verify you're working with the modular system before making changes 